1
00:00:00,767 --> 00:00:03,633
[DRAMATIC TENSE MUSIC PLAYING]

2
00:00:08,300 --> 00:00:09,500
You want Paolo's position?

3
00:00:09,633 --> 00:00:11,200
Do you think Dad would
agree to all of this?

4
00:00:11,333 --> 00:00:13,467
That is exactly why I need
your help.

5
00:00:13,600 --> 00:00:15,933
Together, we will rule
Torrecampo Realty.

6
00:00:16,067 --> 00:00:17,467
Why are you talking
to my sibling?

7
00:00:17,600 --> 00:00:19,100
What are you after this time?

8
00:00:19,233 --> 00:00:22,900
I want to talk to you properly
to thank you

9
00:00:23,033 --> 00:00:26,367
but I will never forget
the cruelty you did to me.

10
00:00:26,500 --> 00:00:28,067
Karma is real, Thea.

11
00:00:28,200 --> 00:00:31,300
So pray that it does not
come for you.

12
00:00:31,433 --> 00:00:32,900
The heavens are punishing me.

13
00:00:33,033 --> 00:00:34,567
While Jasmine is getting better,

14
00:00:34,733 --> 00:00:36,533
this is happening to Ashley.

15
00:00:36,667 --> 00:00:39,767
This is your fault for
what happened to my child.

16
00:00:39,900 --> 00:00:41,133
Edward, we did not expect...

17
00:00:41,267 --> 00:00:42,833
Do not give me excuses
that you did not expect

18
00:00:42,967 --> 00:00:43,833
what could happen to her.

19
00:00:43,967 --> 00:00:45,367
You will answer in court.

20
00:01:33,800 --> 00:01:35,600
How is your child, Edward?

21
00:01:38,000 --> 00:01:39,300
She is still in the hospital.

22
00:01:39,433 --> 00:01:40,700
Under observation.

23
00:01:42,067 --> 00:01:45,167
In case there are side effects
from the bone marrow harvest.

24
00:01:47,167 --> 00:01:48,767
Well, it does not sound
too good.

25
00:01:50,033 --> 00:01:51,600
And you do not look good either.

26
00:01:54,600 --> 00:01:56,767
What even happened to your face?

27
00:01:56,900 --> 00:01:58,500
This is because of Paolo.

28
00:01:59,633 --> 00:02:02,833
He is also the reason Ashley
still has not come home.

29
00:02:05,967 --> 00:02:07,867
It was still not enough
for him

30
00:02:08,000 --> 00:02:10,000
that he humiliated me.

31
00:02:10,133 --> 00:02:12,233
He even put my child's life
in danger.

32
00:02:12,367 --> 00:02:16,000
[INTENSE]

33
00:02:16,167 --> 00:02:18,733
Every time I hear stories
about Paolo,

34
00:02:18,867 --> 00:02:20,867
it is always trouble.

35
00:02:21,000 --> 00:02:23,700
And it just keeps getting worse
and worse.

36
00:02:27,167 --> 00:02:28,933
Do you want revenge on him?

37
00:02:32,033 --> 00:02:33,000
What is your plan?

38
00:02:35,167 --> 00:02:38,133
I need your help to get
the board's vote

39
00:02:38,267 --> 00:02:42,267
to remove Paolo as CEO.

40
00:02:42,400 --> 00:02:44,367
And to put me in his place.

41
00:02:44,500 --> 00:02:46,700
You want Paolo's position?

42
00:02:46,833 --> 00:02:48,167
Are you out of your mind?

43
00:02:48,333 --> 00:02:50,433
Do you think Dad
would allow this?

44
00:02:50,567 --> 00:02:52,867
That is why I need your help.

45
00:02:54,533 --> 00:02:56,267
If we succeed,

46
00:02:58,000 --> 00:03:00,733
I will give you your power back
in your company.

47
00:03:02,333 --> 00:03:05,067
Together, we will rule
Torrecampo Realty.

48
00:03:05,200 --> 00:03:08,367
[INTENSE]

49
00:03:08,500 --> 00:03:09,600
Now tell me,

50
00:03:11,167 --> 00:03:13,333
are we in this together?

51
00:03:13,467 --> 00:03:20,133
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

52
00:03:20,300 --> 00:03:25,300
[INTENSE]

53
00:03:35,500 --> 00:03:37,700
I am glad your transplant
was successful.

54
00:03:40,067 --> 00:03:41,833
You know she loves you so much.

55
00:03:43,567 --> 00:03:45,367
She defied her parents

56
00:03:45,500 --> 00:03:47,700
just to donate to you.

57
00:03:47,833 --> 00:03:50,000
That is how much she cares
about you, Jas.

58
00:03:51,700 --> 00:03:55,000
I will thank her
once I am discharged.

59
00:03:55,167 --> 00:03:57,967
Which hotel are they staying in?

60
00:03:58,100 --> 00:04:01,367
She is still
in this hospital, Jas.

61
00:04:01,500 --> 00:04:03,233
What? She was supposed
to be okay the night

62
00:04:03,367 --> 00:04:05,267
after the procedure.

63
00:04:05,400 --> 00:04:07,267
She had to stay.

64
00:04:07,400 --> 00:04:09,067
Because she developed a fever.

65
00:04:10,733 --> 00:04:14,167
They are checking
for infections.

66
00:04:15,667 --> 00:04:17,300
Plus,

67
00:04:17,433 --> 00:04:19,633
her leg still needs
to heal from the accident.

68
00:04:25,133 --> 00:04:27,733
Can I visit my donor?

69
00:04:27,900 --> 00:04:30,033
Just in another room.

70
00:04:30,167 --> 00:04:32,867
We need to inform the doctor.

71
00:04:33,000 --> 00:04:35,667
Please, just for a bit.

72
00:04:35,800 --> 00:04:37,133
Excuse me.

73
00:04:37,267 --> 00:04:38,633
Yes, Ma'am?

74
00:04:40,033 --> 00:04:43,900
- What happened?
- Your child wants to go out.

75
00:04:44,033 --> 00:04:46,900
- I will handle this.
- Thank you.

76
00:04:50,433 --> 00:04:51,433
I'll go.

77
00:04:54,267 --> 00:04:55,500
What's wrong?

78
00:04:58,167 --> 00:05:01,000
I heard Ash is still
in recovery.

79
00:05:04,233 --> 00:05:07,133
I have no idea,
how did you know?

80
00:05:07,267 --> 00:05:09,267
Is she going to be okay, Mom?

81
00:05:09,400 --> 00:05:13,433
I said many bad things to her.

82
00:05:15,333 --> 00:05:18,267
I feel guilty after she gave me
her stem cells.

83
00:05:18,400 --> 00:05:22,467
And now, I think she's having
a problem after the transplant.

84
00:05:22,600 --> 00:05:25,267
Jasmine, if there were problems,

85
00:05:25,400 --> 00:05:28,500
her mother
would be here already.

86
00:05:28,633 --> 00:05:30,300
I am sure she is okay.

87
00:05:31,333 --> 00:05:32,700
I guess.

88
00:05:32,833 --> 00:05:35,633
I still want to talk to her.

89
00:05:35,800 --> 00:05:39,033
I do not think
that is a good idea.

90
00:05:39,167 --> 00:05:42,933
Uncle Edward and Aunt Thea
do not want it.

91
00:05:49,033 --> 00:05:51,000
Do you really want to go to her?

92
00:05:52,100 --> 00:05:54,567
Even if they get angry at you?

93
00:05:55,633 --> 00:05:58,267
I want to thank her.

94
00:05:58,400 --> 00:06:01,000
For her sacrifice.

95
00:06:01,133 --> 00:06:04,600
I think Auntie Thea
will still give a chance.

96
00:06:04,733 --> 00:06:07,900
Since I now she won't change
her mind about helping me.

97
00:06:09,733 --> 00:06:10,733
Please?

98
00:06:10,867 --> 00:06:12,767
[DRAMATIC]

99
00:06:12,900 --> 00:06:15,467
Be careful, okay.

100
00:06:15,600 --> 00:06:17,033
Does anything hurt?

101
00:06:17,167 --> 00:06:20,500
- Nothing.
- Don't you have feel anything.

102
00:06:22,267 --> 00:06:24,367
Be careful.

103
00:06:24,500 --> 00:06:26,867
It's good,
you are getting better.

104
00:06:27,000 --> 00:06:29,700
Be careful, okay.

105
00:06:29,833 --> 00:06:31,467
Okay.

106
00:06:31,600 --> 00:06:33,333
- Okay.
- Are you okay?

107
00:06:33,467 --> 00:06:35,400
Good job.

108
00:06:35,533 --> 00:06:37,033
Thank you.

109
00:06:38,067 --> 00:06:41,500
I'll come back tomorrow
to check her.

110
00:06:41,667 --> 00:06:43,433
Okay, thank you.

111
00:06:45,900 --> 00:06:46,867
Mom,

112
00:06:48,200 --> 00:06:50,900
why are you forcing me
to stay?

113
00:06:51,033 --> 00:06:54,100
I no longer have a fever.

114
00:06:54,233 --> 00:06:56,433
Why we still need to stay?

115
00:06:56,567 --> 00:06:59,100
My child, I'm not forcing you.

116
00:06:59,233 --> 00:07:03,367
I just want to make sure
there are no side effects.

117
00:07:03,500 --> 00:07:07,033
The doctor also said they still
need to observe you.

118
00:07:07,167 --> 00:07:12,700
Or maybe you want them
to feel guilty.

119
00:07:14,467 --> 00:07:18,200
So what if that is true?

120
00:07:18,333 --> 00:07:19,933
Just let them worry.

121
00:07:20,067 --> 00:07:21,667
This is their fault anyway.

122
00:07:21,800 --> 00:07:24,833
- They deserve it.
- Mom.

123
00:07:24,967 --> 00:07:26,633
[KNOCKING]

124
00:07:31,233 --> 00:07:33,067
Jas?

125
00:07:33,200 --> 00:07:35,633
What are you doing here?

126
00:07:35,767 --> 00:07:38,667
Jas wanted to visit Ashley.

127
00:07:38,800 --> 00:07:41,533
Thea, can I talk to you?

128
00:07:41,667 --> 00:07:45,267
[INTENSE]

129
00:07:50,067 --> 00:07:52,300
Thank you for letting Jas
talk to Ashley.

130
00:07:52,433 --> 00:07:55,500
It is right for her
to say thank you.

131
00:07:55,633 --> 00:08:00,700
If not for my child,
we would be mourning your child.

132
00:08:00,833 --> 00:08:02,433
You are right.

133
00:08:02,567 --> 00:08:05,667
I also want to thank you.

134
00:08:05,800 --> 00:08:08,033
I know you agreed at first.

135
00:08:08,167 --> 00:08:11,833
I know you took it back
when you almost lost Ashley.

136
00:08:13,033 --> 00:08:15,200
I know

137
00:08:15,333 --> 00:08:17,567
you have a soft heart.

138
00:08:22,567 --> 00:08:26,167
Will you stop the drama, Marj?

139
00:08:26,300 --> 00:08:28,900
I know you're still mad at me.

140
00:08:29,033 --> 00:08:30,667
Maybe you forget.

141
00:08:30,800 --> 00:08:32,933
You smashed my face.

142
00:08:34,400 --> 00:08:36,767
I know you think we are even.

143
00:08:36,900 --> 00:08:40,933
And that Ashley's help paid
for your sins.

144
00:08:54,767 --> 00:08:58,567
I am sorry for being rude, Ash.

145
00:09:00,000 --> 00:09:01,833
You are right.

146
00:09:01,967 --> 00:09:05,767
I let our bond be ruined
because of a guy.

147
00:09:07,433 --> 00:09:09,900
I miss our friendship.

148
00:09:14,700 --> 00:09:17,433
I miss it too, Jas.

149
00:09:17,567 --> 00:09:19,233
I miss you already.

150
00:09:21,367 --> 00:09:24,000
Are you not angry at me anymore?

151
00:09:24,133 --> 00:09:29,400
I won't deny that I'm no longer
angry about how you fooled me.

152
00:09:29,567 --> 00:09:32,600
I have not forgiven you yet.

153
00:09:34,167 --> 00:09:35,333
But you're right.

154
00:09:36,600 --> 00:09:39,733
But Ashley's act
is enough repayment.

155
00:09:39,867 --> 00:09:42,367
I don't think a child life
is the price,

156
00:09:42,500 --> 00:09:45,933
on what I and Paolo did to you,
Marj.

157
00:09:46,067 --> 00:09:48,900
Ashley is not at fault.

158
00:09:49,033 --> 00:09:51,000
I agree, Thea.

159
00:09:51,133 --> 00:09:54,200
That is why, I want to talk
to you properly.

160
00:09:54,333 --> 00:09:56,100
To thank you.

161
00:09:56,233 --> 00:10:00,133
I want to apologize.

162
00:10:01,433 --> 00:10:02,967
No.

163
00:10:03,100 --> 00:10:06,533
I do not care if Xander
likes you.

164
00:10:06,667 --> 00:10:08,133
I accept that

165
00:10:08,267 --> 00:10:10,333
I am not his type.

166
00:10:11,900 --> 00:10:14,133
And now I'll getting better
because of you,

167
00:10:14,267 --> 00:10:17,067
I have more chances now
to meet new people.

168
00:10:17,200 --> 00:10:19,367
[LAUGH]

169
00:10:23,400 --> 00:10:27,067
But I will not forget
what you did to me.

170
00:10:28,167 --> 00:10:30,700
Karma is real.

171
00:10:30,833 --> 00:10:34,200
So pray it does not come to you.

172
00:10:41,133 --> 00:10:44,233
I just want thing to go back
to the way they were, Ash.

173
00:10:46,467 --> 00:10:47,667
Me too.

174
00:10:49,400 --> 00:10:51,633
You are still my sister, Jas.

175
00:10:53,100 --> 00:10:56,200
You are my real sister, Ash.

176
00:10:56,333 --> 00:10:58,367
Thank you for saving me.

177
00:10:58,500 --> 00:11:00,233
I owe you my life.

178
00:11:00,367 --> 00:11:04,633
[DRAMATIC]

179
00:11:25,533 --> 00:11:28,100
Sorry I only visited now.

180
00:11:28,233 --> 00:11:29,933
Aunt Marj.

181
00:11:31,333 --> 00:11:32,833
It is okay.

182
00:11:34,000 --> 00:11:35,967
I know the reason.

183
00:11:37,400 --> 00:11:40,700
We owe you so much.

184
00:11:41,767 --> 00:11:44,233
Do not say that.

185
00:11:44,367 --> 00:11:46,367
What I paid for
is still not enough

186
00:11:46,500 --> 00:11:49,900
to make up for all the wrongs
Mom did to your family.

187
00:11:51,400 --> 00:11:52,433
Ash.

188
00:11:52,567 --> 00:11:55,133
I repeat it to you again,
my child.

189
00:11:55,267 --> 00:11:57,900
I have no resentment toward you.

190
00:11:58,033 --> 00:12:00,900
You did nothing wrong.

191
00:12:01,033 --> 00:12:02,633
It is not your fault
that you were born

192
00:12:02,767 --> 00:12:05,967
from your mother's mistake
and my spouse.

193
00:12:06,100 --> 00:12:10,267
[DRAMATIC]

194
00:12:43,633 --> 00:12:44,833
If everything goes smoothly,

195
00:12:45,200 --> 00:12:46,533
I promise to keep my word.

196
00:12:50,000 --> 00:12:50,967
Yes, Sir?

197
00:12:51,100 --> 00:12:53,067
Reservation for three,
under Paolo Torrecampo.

198
00:12:53,200 --> 00:12:54,500
Okay, Sir, I will just prepare
the table.

199
00:12:54,633 --> 00:12:55,867
Thank you.

200
00:12:58,700 --> 00:12:59,700
Nice to see you again.

201
00:12:59,833 --> 00:13:04,367
[INTENSE]

202
00:13:16,600 --> 00:13:18,500
What are you up to this time?

203
00:13:19,967 --> 00:13:21,867
Why are you talking
to my sibling?

204
00:13:23,433 --> 00:13:25,533
Edward and I go way back.

205
00:13:27,067 --> 00:13:28,700
What is your problem, Paolo?

206
00:13:30,233 --> 00:13:32,667
You and Edward

207
00:13:32,800 --> 00:13:34,333
go way back.

208
00:13:35,833 --> 00:13:37,167
What does that mean?

209
00:13:38,667 --> 00:13:40,400
Edward has been helping me
for a long time

210
00:13:40,533 --> 00:13:43,300
when it comes
to Torrecampo Realty.

211
00:13:43,433 --> 00:13:45,333
With what has been working

212
00:13:45,467 --> 00:13:47,000
and what has not.

213
00:13:48,200 --> 00:13:50,200
And which easy projects to take.

214
00:13:52,367 --> 00:13:55,467
Did he also help you to take
the Menagerie Project from me?

215
00:14:01,133 --> 00:14:02,400
You know, Paolo,

216
00:14:04,200 --> 00:14:06,800
I wish you luck
in the near future.

217
00:14:08,500 --> 00:14:09,900
You will need it.

218
00:14:16,033 --> 00:14:18,633
Ash, we are going back
to our room now, okay?

219
00:14:20,833 --> 00:14:23,233
DM me once you are discharged.

220
00:14:23,367 --> 00:14:25,800
I hope we get to see each other
again before you go.

221
00:14:25,933 --> 00:14:27,167
Of course.

222
00:14:29,733 --> 00:14:32,667
[UNSETTLING]

223
00:14:34,233 --> 00:14:36,333
Ash, are you okay?

224
00:14:36,467 --> 00:14:37,833
I'm okay.

225
00:14:42,667 --> 00:14:44,067
You are burning up.

226
00:14:46,967 --> 00:14:48,033
Ash?

227
00:14:49,200 --> 00:14:50,367
Ash.

228
00:14:50,500 --> 00:14:51,667
Oh my god!

229
00:14:51,800 --> 00:14:53,033
Ash!

230
00:14:53,167 --> 00:14:54,233
Ashley!

231
00:14:54,367 --> 00:14:55,233
Ashley!

232
00:14:55,367 --> 00:14:58,400
- Help! Help us!
- My child!

233
00:14:58,533 --> 00:14:59,700
What is happening to you?

234
00:14:59,833 --> 00:15:01,300
- My child!
- Help!

235
00:15:01,467 --> 00:15:02,433
Help!

236
00:15:02,567 --> 00:15:03,967
Nurse!

237
00:15:04,100 --> 00:15:05,667
- Nurse!
- Help, please!

238
00:15:05,800 --> 00:15:08,167
[INTENSE]

239
00:15:08,300 --> 00:15:10,533
Nurse! What is happening
to my child?

240
00:15:10,667 --> 00:15:12,100
Ma'am.

241
00:15:12,233 --> 00:15:13,433
What? Wait.

242
00:15:13,567 --> 00:15:14,800
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

243
00:15:14,933 --> 00:15:15,933
No!

244
00:15:16,067 --> 00:15:17,033
My child!

245
00:15:17,167 --> 00:15:19,433
- [INDISTINCT CHATTER]
- No! I am not leaving.

246
00:15:19,567 --> 00:15:22,700
Wait, I need to know what
is happening to my child.

247
00:15:22,833 --> 00:15:24,300
We are sorry, sorry.

248
00:15:24,433 --> 00:15:25,433
My child!

249
00:15:25,567 --> 00:15:30,067
[INTENSE]

250
00:15:36,500 --> 00:15:40,633
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

251
00:15:47,967 --> 00:15:50,467
I am willing to give you
my share of the company.

252
00:15:50,600 --> 00:15:52,433
So you will have enough power

253
00:15:52,567 --> 00:15:54,433
to do what I need you to do.

254
00:15:54,567 --> 00:15:56,100
I am certain about this.

255
00:15:56,233 --> 00:15:57,933
You yourselves said

256
00:15:58,067 --> 00:16:00,400
Paolo is becoming a liability
to the company.

257
00:16:00,533 --> 00:16:03,967
And I think, this is better
in the long run.

258
00:16:04,100 --> 00:16:05,400
You handle the execution

259
00:16:05,533 --> 00:16:09,133
and how this will be done as
long as I see my brother

260
00:16:09,300 --> 00:16:13,067
removed as CEO and replaced
by Aldrin Castelo.

261
00:16:17,433 --> 00:16:18,567
Then we have a deal.

262
00:16:20,100 --> 00:16:21,600
Read through the papers.

263
00:16:21,733 --> 00:16:24,733
[INTENSE]

264
00:16:24,867 --> 00:16:25,767
Then we sign it.

265
00:16:25,900 --> 00:16:27,833
Nothing in the agreement
will change.

266
00:16:27,967 --> 00:16:28,967
Is that clear?

267
00:16:31,900 --> 00:16:36,100
[PHONE RINGING]

268
00:16:38,300 --> 00:16:42,133
[PHONE RINGING]

269
00:16:43,667 --> 00:16:44,567
Thea?

270
00:16:48,967 --> 00:16:49,900
What?

271
00:16:52,767 --> 00:16:54,667
Is she going to be okay, Mom?

272
00:16:54,800 --> 00:16:58,067
Maybe we should go back
and make sure Ashley is okay.

273
00:16:58,200 --> 00:16:59,533
I will handle it, my child.

274
00:16:59,667 --> 00:17:01,533
You need to rest.

275
00:17:02,800 --> 00:17:03,967
Marj!

276
00:17:06,133 --> 00:17:07,833
This is your fault!

277
00:17:07,967 --> 00:17:09,567
Thea.

278
00:17:09,700 --> 00:17:12,600
This is your fault
for what happened to my child!

279
00:17:12,733 --> 00:17:14,667
Thea, do not blame my child.

280
00:17:14,800 --> 00:17:16,100
She is innocent.

281
00:17:16,267 --> 00:17:18,433
Direct your anger at me.

282
00:17:18,567 --> 00:17:20,167
Do not drag her into this.

283
00:17:21,833 --> 00:17:26,000
Marj, it should only
be your child who gets sick.

284
00:17:27,100 --> 00:17:29,267
Not my child.

285
00:17:31,067 --> 00:17:34,500
My child is convulsing
and I cannot do anything!

286
00:17:37,367 --> 00:17:40,733
If anyone dragged an innocent
person into this, it was you.

287
00:17:43,300 --> 00:17:46,800
And if a child should die,
it should be your child!

288
00:17:48,100 --> 00:17:49,467
Mom.

289
00:17:49,633 --> 00:17:52,233
It's okay, let's just go.

290
00:17:52,367 --> 00:17:56,633
[INTENSE]

291
00:17:58,133 --> 00:18:00,700
Be thankful my child stopped me.

292
00:18:01,867 --> 00:18:03,767
I understand you,

293
00:18:03,900 --> 00:18:05,900
you are just worried
about Ashley.

294
00:18:06,033 --> 00:18:08,567
I will accept your anger.

295
00:18:08,700 --> 00:18:11,667
But never say that again.

296
00:18:11,800 --> 00:18:14,133
Because if those words leave
your mouth again,

297
00:18:14,267 --> 00:18:15,933
I will not back down.

298
00:18:16,067 --> 00:18:20,100
[INTENSE]

299
00:18:26,700 --> 00:18:29,967
[SOBBING]

300
00:18:31,567 --> 00:18:35,800
[DRAMATIC]

301
00:18:55,200 --> 00:18:57,467
What if Aunt Thea is right?

302
00:18:57,600 --> 00:18:59,233
What if something worse happens
to Ashley

303
00:18:59,367 --> 00:19:01,000
and it is all because of me?

304
00:19:01,133 --> 00:19:02,000
Jas,

305
00:19:02,133 --> 00:19:04,333
it is not your fault.

306
00:19:04,467 --> 00:19:05,833
Okay?

307
00:19:08,200 --> 00:19:09,400
Me.

308
00:19:10,500 --> 00:19:12,000
I am the one at fault.

309
00:19:15,500 --> 00:19:17,867
I know you agree
with this, Marj.

310
00:19:19,167 --> 00:19:20,633
This is my fault.

311
00:19:22,667 --> 00:19:25,667
If only I had been faithful
to you as a spouse,

312
00:19:28,933 --> 00:19:31,333
we would not have ended up
like this.

313
00:19:32,933 --> 00:19:34,400
Edward is right.

314
00:19:37,433 --> 00:19:39,667
The heavens are punishing me

315
00:19:39,800 --> 00:19:41,667
for the shameful things I did
to you.

316
00:19:44,933 --> 00:19:46,967
While Jasmine is getting better,

317
00:19:49,800 --> 00:19:51,867
this is happening to Ashley.

318
00:19:53,300 --> 00:19:54,867
- [THUMPING]
- Dad.

319
00:19:55,000 --> 00:19:57,467
- Dad, stop!
- Stop it, please.

320
00:19:59,400 --> 00:20:00,733
I deserve to suffer!

321
00:20:00,867 --> 00:20:03,067
I deserve to be punished.

322
00:20:03,233 --> 00:20:07,533
Ashley does not deserve
to carry all your punishment.

323
00:20:07,667 --> 00:20:11,200
The least thing we can do right
now is to pray for her.

324
00:20:11,333 --> 00:20:14,500
Just like we always
do for Jasmine.

325
00:20:14,633 --> 00:20:18,733
[DRAMATIC]

326
00:20:32,533 --> 00:20:33,500
All right.

327
00:20:33,633 --> 00:20:36,500
Just keep me posted
about Ashley's condition.

328
00:20:40,133 --> 00:20:43,900
I cannot believe Marj
did that to poor Ashley.

329
00:20:45,300 --> 00:20:46,700
How did that procedure
go through

330
00:20:46,833 --> 00:20:48,967
without her parents' consent?

331
00:20:50,133 --> 00:20:51,533
They have consent.

332
00:20:52,633 --> 00:20:54,133
From Thea.

333
00:20:54,267 --> 00:20:57,433
She agreed to let Ashley
get tested

334
00:20:57,567 --> 00:20:59,700
and donate to Jasmine

335
00:20:59,833 --> 00:21:05,033
in exchange for several million
pesos I would give their family.

336
00:21:05,167 --> 00:21:06,800
You know, Greg, did you not
think that

337
00:21:06,933 --> 00:21:08,633
because of how you act,

338
00:21:08,800 --> 00:21:11,433
Edward holds resentment
toward you?

339
00:21:11,567 --> 00:21:14,367
I should have disowned
that boy a long time ago.

340
00:21:15,533 --> 00:21:18,133
You cannot lose a child
and not treat his wounds

341
00:21:18,267 --> 00:21:20,600
and then wonder why he does not
run to you.

342
00:21:22,567 --> 00:21:26,967
You never showed even
a little love for him.

343
00:21:27,100 --> 00:21:28,167
[HUFFS]

344
00:21:29,967 --> 00:21:32,000
How can I love that child

345
00:21:32,133 --> 00:21:34,667
when every time I look at him,

346
00:21:35,767 --> 00:21:37,200
all I can think about

347
00:21:37,333 --> 00:21:39,300
is what you did to me?

348
00:21:39,433 --> 00:21:43,033
- [SIGHS]
- [INTENSE]

349
00:21:50,633 --> 00:21:51,867
Greg,

350
00:21:52,000 --> 00:21:54,467
that issue has long been over.

351
00:21:55,600 --> 00:21:57,500
I already regretted that.

352
00:21:59,300 --> 00:22:00,767
Do not make

353
00:22:00,900 --> 00:22:02,633
Edward pay

354
00:22:02,767 --> 00:22:06,667
for a mistake I already paid
for a long time ago.

355
00:22:08,933 --> 00:22:11,100
[LAUGHING]

356
00:22:12,633 --> 00:22:14,633
Look at you.

357
00:22:14,800 --> 00:22:17,067
Trying to reason with me

358
00:22:17,200 --> 00:22:19,633
when you were just playing
with my emotions

359
00:22:19,767 --> 00:22:24,667
and blackmailing me over my
indiscretions a few weeks ago.

360
00:22:24,800 --> 00:22:27,267
Sad, silly woman.

361
00:22:27,400 --> 00:22:28,267
Silly,

362
00:22:28,400 --> 00:22:29,267
silly,

363
00:22:29,400 --> 00:22:30,667
silly.

364
00:22:30,800 --> 00:22:33,433
[LAUGHING]

365
00:22:33,567 --> 00:22:34,633
Regina.

366
00:22:34,767 --> 00:22:36,367
[LAUGHING]

367
00:22:38,267 --> 00:22:40,833
[LAUGHING CONTINUES]

368
00:22:40,967 --> 00:22:44,967
[INTENSE]

369
00:22:50,900 --> 00:22:53,033
Post-procedural complication?

370
00:22:53,167 --> 00:22:56,233
Yes, it is possible
that there is bacteria

371
00:22:56,367 --> 00:22:59,400
in her bloodstream affecting
her brain.

372
00:23:02,067 --> 00:23:04,300
Is that why she had a seizure?

373
00:23:04,433 --> 00:23:06,167
Doctor, is that not dangerous?

374
00:23:07,200 --> 00:23:10,433
For now, the patient needs
close monitoring

375
00:23:10,567 --> 00:23:13,033
because her condition
is rapidly worsening.

376
00:23:13,167 --> 00:23:18,067
We are giving immediate
treatment for the complications.

377
00:23:18,200 --> 00:23:19,167
Excuse me.

378
00:23:19,300 --> 00:23:23,600
[DRAMATIC]

379
00:23:24,733 --> 00:23:26,700
She is going to be okay.

380
00:23:26,833 --> 00:23:28,600
We will find a solution.

381
00:23:32,933 --> 00:23:34,667
- This is Marj's fault.
- [SOBBING]

382
00:23:34,800 --> 00:23:38,333
[DRAMATIC]

383
00:23:38,467 --> 00:23:42,500
We might lose our child because
they forced Ashley to donate.

384
00:23:48,967 --> 00:23:50,100
Edward,

385
00:23:52,900 --> 00:23:55,367
if you want to prove

386
00:23:55,533 --> 00:23:58,000
that you are a capable parent

387
00:23:58,133 --> 00:24:00,700
and if you truly love Ashley,

388
00:24:02,467 --> 00:24:04,367
do something about this.

389
00:24:06,833 --> 00:24:10,467
Make sure Marj pays

390
00:24:10,600 --> 00:24:12,233
for what was done to my child.

391
00:24:12,367 --> 00:24:15,500
[INTENSE]

392
00:24:19,500 --> 00:24:25,500
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

393
00:24:37,267 --> 00:24:38,933
Edward!

394
00:24:39,067 --> 00:24:40,467
Edward, we did not
expect that...

395
00:24:40,600 --> 00:24:42,133
You did not expect it?

396
00:24:42,267 --> 00:24:43,600
That is why Thea did not want
her to get tested

397
00:24:43,733 --> 00:24:45,533
as a match in the first place.

398
00:24:45,667 --> 00:24:46,667
So do not give me the excuse

399
00:24:46,800 --> 00:24:48,767
that you did not expect
what could happen to her.

400
00:24:50,500 --> 00:24:51,533
Edward, we want to help.

401
00:24:51,667 --> 00:24:53,867
- We will do everything to...
- For sure!

402
00:24:54,000 --> 00:24:55,367
You need to!

403
00:24:55,500 --> 00:24:56,700
And I will make sure

404
00:24:56,833 --> 00:24:59,033
you answer in court.

405
00:24:59,167 --> 00:25:01,133
Are you really going
to take it that far?

406
00:25:01,267 --> 00:25:03,367
Edward, this is a family matter.

407
00:25:03,533 --> 00:25:07,467
I am hiring a legal team
to help me sue you for coercion,

408
00:25:07,600 --> 00:25:09,267
exploitation of a minor.

409
00:25:09,400 --> 00:25:11,500
That is on top
of criminal battery.

410
00:25:11,633 --> 00:25:13,533
Because of what happened
to Ashley.

411
00:25:13,667 --> 00:25:15,900
Edward, I am sorry.

412
00:25:16,033 --> 00:25:18,433
You cannot even hire
a legal team.

413
00:25:18,567 --> 00:25:21,200
And another thing, Dad will not
help you either

414
00:25:21,333 --> 00:25:23,667
because this will damage
the family name.

415
00:25:23,800 --> 00:25:27,033
And who told you that I cannot
afford a legal team?

416
00:25:28,900 --> 00:25:31,033
Just wait for my lawyer
to talk to you.

417
00:25:31,167 --> 00:25:35,200
[INTENSE]

418
00:25:42,467 --> 00:25:46,867
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

419
00:25:50,800 --> 00:25:51,567
Ashley.

420
00:25:51,700 --> 00:25:52,967
Ash, what is happening?

421
00:25:53,100 --> 00:25:54,567
What happened to you?

422
00:25:54,700 --> 00:25:58,167
My child, my child,
what is happening to you?

423
00:25:58,300 --> 00:26:00,800
- My child.
- Resume CPR.

424
00:26:00,933 --> 00:26:02,867
Do not leave us yet, my child.

425
00:26:03,000 --> 00:26:06,467
I will make sure that every tear
we are crying now

426
00:26:06,600 --> 00:26:09,800
will be paid for by the people
who did this to you, my child.

427
00:26:09,967 --> 00:26:12,033
Why, Edward? Where is your
arrogance now?

428
00:26:12,167 --> 00:26:13,600
What did I do to you?

429
00:26:13,733 --> 00:26:16,400
For you to treat me
like trash, Dad?

430
00:26:16,533 --> 00:26:17,767
When you treat me

431
00:26:17,900 --> 00:26:19,733
like I am not your real child.

432
00:26:19,867 --> 00:26:21,233
Do you want to know why?

433
00:26:21,367 --> 00:26:22,300
I want to know.

434
00:26:22,433 --> 00:26:23,400
I want to know!

435
00:26:23,533 --> 00:26:24,833
You want the truth?

436
00:26:26,167 --> 00:26:27,500
Fine, do what you want.

437
00:26:27,633 --> 00:26:28,967
I do not even care about Dad.

438
00:26:29,100 --> 00:26:31,067
He abandoned me,
I am just here because

439
00:26:31,200 --> 00:26:32,733
I wanted to ask you for help.

440
00:26:32,867 --> 00:26:34,400
And you still have the nerve
to boast?

441
00:26:34,533 --> 00:26:36,067
After what you did.

442
00:26:36,200 --> 00:26:37,933
You know why I am like this
toward Edward!

443
00:26:38,067 --> 00:26:39,233
I know.

444
00:26:39,367 --> 00:26:42,567
And until now,
you are still wrong.

445
00:26:42,733 --> 00:26:45,533
He is not your blood.

446
00:26:45,667 --> 00:26:48,000
He is not a real Torrecampo.
